description.plain:
Morphing between the alternative rap styles of the late 2010s, Florida-based rapper $NOT built his name with a relaxed approach to the era’s trap sonics.

Making his musical debut with the July 2016 single “By Myself,” rapper $NOT’s early career was defined by the D.I.Y. ethos of the era. Dipping his toes into numerous key scenes, the rapper’s early releases varied from Playboi Carti-esque circular trap to the brash, screaming bangers of contemporaries like XXXTentacion. Continuing to adapt and evolve, the young musician spent 2018 on more melancholic terms, adopting a muffled, BONES-esque tone for ironically gloomy singles like “Joyful” and “Mi Vida Loca.” His first project came with the five track EP The Ti$$ue Files; released on April 24, 2018. The EP embodied the lo-fi sonics of his career thus far, providing an experimental mix of lethargic trap anthems.

The rapper’s breakout hit was soon to arrive with the September 2018 single “Gosha,” adopting the laid-back delivery of his signature work thus far, he quickly racked up tens of millions of streams across platforms worldwide. With a strong fan base behind him, the rapper continued to experiment throughout 2019 (even venturing into country-trap for single “Billy Boy”) before kicking off 2020 with his debut album, - TRAGEDY +. True to $NOT’s tried-and-tested approach, the March project included fresh production touches to his blend of chilled-out trap, including key hits “Gosha” and “Beretta.”. In late 2020, $NOT followed his debut up with a sophomore effort Beautiful Havoc which was helmed by lead single “Sangria”.

songs.title: GOSHA

description.plain:
“GOSHA” is $NOT’s 2018 breakout hit. The song quickly gained attention on the internet after a music video for the single was posted by ELEVATOR on YouTube. The track currently peaks at nearly 25 million streams on SoundCloud.

The song is named after Russian clothing brand Gosha Rubchinskiy and finds $NOT rapping about clothing, women, jewelry and about his advantage over opponents.

songs.title: Moon & Stars

description.plain:
On the highly anticipated love song “Moon & Stars,” $NOT invites the girl he’s infatuated with to escape reality and take a dream-like trip with him. The slow and romantic instrumental led by the sample of Lord Huron’s 2015 song “The Night We Met.”

The track was originally strongly teased as a solo song since early 2019. However, the hype generated around “Moon & Stars” drove $NOT to make the song one of his most important releases ever: he revealed that he was waiting for a feature to release the song, which turned out to be a contribution from American singer Maggie Lindemann.

It’s also worth noting that “Moon and Stars” is supported by a music video and was released on all streaming services—which is not insignificant since $NOT is used to releasing songs on SoundCloud.

songs.title: BERETTA

description.plain:
The second TRAGEDY single, “Beretta,” sees $NOT enlist fellow Florida talent wifisfuneral for a catchy, laid-back track about women, guns, and money. The song’s release date marks the one-year anniversary of “GOSHA”—$NOT’s immensely popular first TRAGEDY single, released in September 2018.

Originally a $NOT solo, Weef hopped on “BERETTA” when $NOT in late August of 2019 previewed the track and asked his Instagram followers what artist they thought would make a fitting feature.

Despite how popular the track would become later down the line, it was initially exclusively released on SoundCloud and YouTube, later distributed across all major streaming platforms on September 20, 2019. “BERETTA” received an Omar Jones-directed music video in December 2019.
